<TITLE> 37 die as Kishoreganj boat sinks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kishoregonj, Dec 4 (bdnews24.com)At least 37 people died and scores were missing after a boat capsized on the Srigang river at Mithamoin in Bhairab on Friday. Kishoregonj deputy commissioner Mohammad Shah Alam told bdnews24.com the accident took place at around 9:30am when a Bhairab-bound engine boat collided head-on with passenger ferry MV Al-Helal near Charigram area at Mithamoin upazila. Some 50 passengers of the boat went under water, Alam said. Local people have been carrying out rescue operations since morning. Divers from Dhaka are yet to reach the spot, he added. A ferry, MV Coco-4, partially capsized last Friday, the night before Eid-ul-Azha, at Nazirpur river station in Lalmohan, some 40 km from Bhola district town, killing 85 people and leaving many missing. The vessel, crowded from hull to decks with people heading home to celebrate the holiday with families, began tipping with the weight of disembarking passengers and partially sank. bdnews2
